dcterms:description: The ps2.0 dataset consists of 9827 training images with 9476 parking-slots and 2338 testing images with 2168 parking-slots, collected from typical indoor and outdoor scenes under various environmental conditions, with a resolution of 600 × 600 pixels corresponding to a 10m×10m physical plane region.

dcterms:description: The PSV dataset is used as an out-of-distribution testing dataset to verify the generalization performances of parking-slot detection methods, providing ground truth for evaluation.
dcterms:title: PSV
